    "body": "## Problem\n\nMaybe similar to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38545\nHappened after d5516daf121aa718e79bcd423ee24c24492893c0\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nui2 will be disabled after `:restart`\n```\nnvim --clean --cmd \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({})\"\n```\nThis work as expected:\n```\nnvim --clean --cmd \"au UIEnter * lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({})\"\n```\n\nbecause ui2 is disabled when \"headless\"\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/64d55b74d83d566975e269bed0810d9008119ddf/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2.lua#L175-L177\n\n## Expected behavior\nui2.enable should enable ui2\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2730 g79ebe54634` neovim/neovim@79ebe54634\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.9-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
